Summary: 1991 SIGHTING OF AN OBJECT EXHINITING A SPIRALING OUTWARD FLIGHT.
divs: sighting detailsin 1991 this witness sighted an object which appeared to be the size of venus in the early evening skies over western new york and possibly as far as virginia. the object was bright and travelling in a spiraling outward motion. it was not venus. it was circular\spherical. it was bright but the witness clearly stated it was not star like nor was it venus. the object was first sighted in the south and flew in a norrteast direction.they are not sure of the year or season since approximately 16-17 years passed since the sighting. the witness said they thought there was something in the papers about the object. the newspaper is unknown. they said it was not a "japanese rocket\ satellite". the witness said the light diffused after awhile. it was the odd spiraling motion of the object which caught their eye. the individual has had no prior sightings before or since and no strange dreams or after effects. they have had an interest in the ufo phenomenon because of a great aunt who was interested in the subject back in the 1940's.
